t the quick-connects.<br><br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.base-nine.org/images/otterjoy/MVC-612S.JPG"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>Everthing connects to an I-PAC, which is a keyboard passthrough for pushbutton connectors that doesn't suffer from the &quot;ghosting&quot; problems you get if you canabalize a keyboard.<br><br>If anyone is interested, I'll show off my Opti-PAC connector board, the spinner I've ordered, and other insight into my insanity.<br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>,Guildleader: <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=varulvthewarrior>Varulv the Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/01 5:49:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=733.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> OMFG</span><hr size=1> You are as sick as my brother.<br><br>He built a &quot;arcade box&quot; with a 24 inch tv in it and then a puter in with MAME installed.<br><br>This thing really feels like an arcade machine, but really isnt that going to far to play pacman and time commando?<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Anyways, that joystick seem to be close to the real thing. My brother rebuild a Dreamcast Arcade Controller somehow, he said it had the best feel of the arcade stick out there.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uwarlordocilot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warlord Ocilot</A></span><br> <span 